OL,3,CThe PM's miserable month and
OL,4,CStormont's TACOs
OL,6,FNeedless to say, the Prime Minister's
OL,7,Fin-tray is full and his future is
OL,8,Funclear.
OL,10,FWhile the PM has been fighting for his
OL,11,Fpolitical life, ministers here have
OL,12,Fbeen calling for a meeting with him to
OL,13,Fdiscuss Stormont's financial woes.
OL,15,FThe First and deputy First Ministers
OL,16,Fasked for the meeting with Sir Keir
OL,17,FStarmer last month amid claims the
OL,18,FExecutive's budget was at "breaking
OL,19,Fpoint".
OL,26,@zD@[OU{D@FO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1779642355
OL,3,CThe PM's miserable month and
OL,4,CStormont's TACOs
OL,6,FMinisters have yet to agree a budget
OL,7,Ffor the current financial year and
OL,8,Fhave insisted they need more financial
OL,9,Fsupport from the Treasury to deliver
OL,10,Fspending plans that avoid dramatic
OL,11,Fcuts to public services.
OL,13,FLast week, Michelle O'Neill said they
OL,14,Fstill had not received a response from
OL,15,Fthe PM, but was unrelenting: "We're
OL,16,Fgoing to keep knocking on that door.
OL,17,FWe're going to keep fighting for
OL,18,Fpeople here, because people here
OL,19,Fdeserve support to get them through
OL,20,Fthese tough times."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1779642355
OL,3,CThe PM's miserable month and
OL,4,CStormont's TACOs
OL,6,FEmma Little-Pengelly added: "We do
OL,7,Fneed, as I've said, that support from
OL,8,FTreasury in my view to enable us to
OL,9,Fget that agreed budget.
OL,11,F"So, the sooner that those discussions
OL,12,Fcan happen, the sooner we can get to
OL,13,Fthe position of taking a look at how
OL,14,Fwe can get that budget in place."
OL,16,FA UK Government spokesperson said:
OL,17,F"The Prime Minister is getting on with
OL,18,Fthe job at hand and delivering change
OL,19,Ffor people across the United Kingdom.
OL,26,@sD@AOUvD@aO]yD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
